### 5. Conclusion

The issue is a classic fast-math miscompilation where a transformation, valid under standard floating-point rules, becomes incorrect due to the `ninf` flag. By adding a check to ensure the `fadd` instruction has no fast-math flags, we can prevent this incorrect optimization. This change will fix the reported bug and prevent similar issues in the future.
